headline: CVS taps former UPS executive as finance chief in turnaround push
summary: (Reuters) -CVS Health on Tuesday tapped former UPS executive Brian Newman for the role of finance chief, as new CEO David Joyner strengthens management ranks in his bid to turn around the company.  "A major piece of the CVS stock recovery story revolves around restoring management credibility," said James Harlow, senior vice president at CVS investor Novare Capital Management.  CVS Health shares rose over 8% and were also boosted by bigger-than-expected increase in the U.S. government's reimbursement rates for Medicare Advantage plans in 2026 that lifted shares across the sector.
